- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the framework involves reasoning about spatio-temporal models, which can be seen as a form of AI. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of the framework in cyber-physical systems engineering. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the framework can be applied to decision-making in robotic systems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the use of a formal methods-based framework for decision support, which can be seen as related to programming languages.
